….Assures of transparency, security and peaceful conduct of polls By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Ahead of the governorship election scheduled to hold on Saturday in Ekiti State, the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), said it has deployed four National Commissioners, eight Resident Electoral Commissioners and many senior officials to support its State office in the State to deliver credible elections. This is also as the Commission has given assurances of a transparent poll as well as security and peaceful conduct of the exercise. The INEC Chairman, Prof Mahmood Yakubu gave the assurance on Tuesday during his address at the stakeholders meeting held at the Amazing Grace Events Centre, Ado- Ekiti. The INEC Boss also informed that the Bimodal Voter Accreditation System (BVAS) will be deployed for voter accreditation and uploading of election results to the INEC Result Viewing (IReV) portal on Election Day. He further assured the political parties, candidates and the electorate that the choice of who becomes the next Governor of Ekiti State is entirely in the hands of voters. The electoral umpire expressed concern over the use  of money to induce voters on election day. Stressing that vote buying is a threat to our electoral democracy. To discourage the practice, we have changed the configuration of our polling units to bring the ballot boxes closer to the voting cubicles and also banned the use of mobile phones and photographic devices by voters while in the voting cubicles, the INEC Chairman said. The full speech of the INEC Chairman reads: ADDRESS BY THE HONOURABLE CHAIRMAN, INDEPENDENT NATIONAL ELECTORAL COMMISSION, PROFESSOR MAHMOOD YAKUBU, AT THE EKITI GOVERNORSHIP ELECTION STAKEHOLDERS’ MEETING HELD AT THE AMAZING GRACE EVENTS CENTRE, ADO-EKITI, TUESDAY 14TH JUNE 2022 By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Chairman, Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) Prof Mahmood Yakubu has said that the general security situatio